1. Plan the robbery: Research the bank and its security measures, find out when the bank is most crowded, and decide on the time and date for the robbery.
2. Gather information: Obtain the layout of the bank, including the location of cameras, alarms, and the vault.
3. Get a gun: Acquire a firearm, preferably a handgun. Make sure it is untraceable and in good condition.
4. Wear a disguise: Dress in clothing that will help you blend in with the crowd and not be recognized.
5. Enter the bank: Enter the bank during business hours and with confidence. Avoid drawing attention to yourself by acting suspiciously.
6. Brandish the gun: Once inside the bank, pull out the gun and point it at the teller.
